                                                                            <comments>
                            <comment id="238349" author="adilger" created="Tue, 11 Dec 2018 00:02:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;No activity here in 5 years and this is likely fixed with &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-8708&quot; title=&quot;Grant shrinking disabled all the time&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-8708&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-8708&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="65455" author="adilger" created="Fri, 30 Aug 2013 17:05:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;We don&apos;t actually have OBD_CONNECT_GRANT_SHRINK enabled on the clients in our version of Lustre.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I agree that it shouldn&apos;t be flooding the server with these requests - grant shrinking should only happen occasionally, like on a ping.  The default interval GRANT_SHRINK_INTERVAL is 1200s, but this would be sent from multiple clients if they are idle and not using the grant.  It should only be a one-time event.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
